Command for connecting Local to remote using Git (> --commands)

Create New repository in remote
Create Newfolder in Local, Initiate with
> git init

To see all the commands
> git --help

And update User Name, Mailid in your Git-SCM
> git config --global user.name "username"
> git config --global user.email "email@example.com"

Next to add your remote repository to local, 
> git remote add <URL>

To Add files and Folder use this,(by using "." all file will be added)
> git add .

To check th stuts,
> git status

This will add the change in directory, once done proceed with commit
> git commit -m <message for Commit>

For remote repositoy clone to local
> git clone <HostName> <Remote Repository URL>

Accessing github remote repository from local
> git branch --set-upstream-to origin/my_branch
  This command let you to add your local repo to remote repo
  
Git Checkout to remote Branch to local
> git checkout -b <Local Branch Name> <Clone Remote Branch>
  
Creating new branch
> git branch -b <branch-Name>

Moving to NewBranch or Existing Branch
> git checkout <branch-Name>

Merging Branch to master
> git merge <branch>

rebase
> git rebase <branch Name>

